articles.author: Stella Qiu
articles.description: Asian shares held tight ranges on Wednesday as investors awaited results from tech darling Nvidia to see if the sector's lofty valuations can withstand a jump in bond yields, while still gloomy factory readings from Japan left sentiment fragile.
articles.title: Asian shares sit tight ahead of Nvidia results, yields near highs

articles.author: Yuka Obayashi
articles.description: Oil prices eased in early trade on Wednesday, weighed down by fears U.S. interest rates could stay higher for longer and economic growth could slow further in top crude importer China and hurt fuel demand.
articles.title: Oil prices ease on concerns over rate hikes, China gloom

articles.author: Devayani Sathyan, Sujith Pai
articles.description: India stocks will trade only modestly higher at year-end, according to a Reuters poll of equity analysts who said a correction was likely before then, citing tightening global financial conditions as a risk.
articles.title: Indian stocks set for muted gains by year-end, correction likely: Reuters poll

articles.author: Abigail Summerville, Anirban Sen
articles.description: Private equity firm Roark Capital is in the lead to acquire sandwich chain Subway for well over $9 billion after attaching conditions to some of the windfall the two families that own it will get, people familiar with the matter said on Tuesday.
articles.title: Buyout firm Roark sets conditions to clinch $9 bln-plus Subway deal-sources

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Two tankers, the Singapore-flagged BW Lesmes and Cayman Islands-flagged Burri, briefly collided in Egypt's Suez Canal, ship tracking company Marine Traffic said early Wednesday, citing eyewitnesses.
articles.title: Two tankers collide briefly in Suez Canal

articles.author: Yelin Mo, Max Cherney, Stephen Nellis
articles.description: The upcoming listing of semiconductor technology firm Arm Holdings Ltd is supposed to be strong medicine for what has been ailing the U.S. IPO market, as well as provide a shot in the arm for Arm owner Softbank Group Corp (9984.T).
articles.title: Analysis: Arm's China relationship complicates IPO

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Elon Musk is pushing to change how news links appear on his social media platform X, formerly called Twitter, in a move that could potentially undermine the ability of news publishers to draw audience.
articles.title: Elon Musk's X plans to remove headlines from links to news articles

articles.author: Andrew Hay, Liliana Salgado
articles.description: Deborah Loeffler felt she could not lose much more after a wildfire destroyed the home in Maui where five generations of her family have lived, and a son died the same day on the U.S. mainland.
articles.title: Maui wildfire victims fear land grab may threaten Hawaiian culture

articles.author: Bhargav Acharya, Gabriel Araujo
articles.description: BRICS leaders met on Tuesday to plot the future course of the bloc of developing nations but divisions re-emerged ahead of a critical debate over a potential expansion of the group intended to boost its global clout.
articles.title: BRICS divisions re-emerge ahead of critical expansion debate

articles.author: Jack Queen
articles.description: The first of Donald Trump's co-defendants in Georgia's criminal case accusing the former U.S. president and his associates of subverting his 2020 election loss surrendered at an Atlanta jail on Tuesday, according to county records and a statement.
articles.title: First Trump allies in Georgia election subversion case surrender
